BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ride the Loop
DTSTART:20260419T130000Z
DTEND:20260419T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T173545Z
UID:1768d7d5-8102-5fd7-8f58-52628eeaa317
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, April 19\, 2026\n\nJoin us for our 72km Ride the Loop
  event.\n\nStart from The Well at 486 Front St W in front of Fix Coffee + 
 Bikes.\n\nWhat is The Loop?\n\nThe Loop trail is an ALMOST complete 72km c
 ircuit of trails that includes the waterfront\, Humber River\, Finch Hydro
  Corridor\, and Don River trails. Unfortunately\, there are about ten smal
 l gaps that undermine the value of The Loop Trail for everyday/utilitarian
 \, recreational\, and tourism cyclists. The Loop Trail is part of the city
 's Ravine Strategy\, although the gaps are all on roads. The Loop was firs
 t announced by the city in 2020\, but there has been little progress -- un
 til the launch of our advocacy campaign and ride in November 2025.\n\nYou 
 can ride with us for the full 72km\, or join us at various locations.\n\nS
 ubject to minor adjustments\, here is our anticipated route: https://maps.
 app.goo.gl/97RLNh7uf4JBtw5u7\n\nTo register\, please email (mailto:Communi
 ty.Bikeways.Toronto@gmail.com) Community.Bikeways.Toronto@gmail.com\n\n\n\
 nAn approximate itinerary will be sent to registrants.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n#blo
 ck-b8b758de027f728d7d53 { } #block-b8b758de027f728d7d53 .sqs-html-content 
 { } #block-b8b758de027f728d7d53 { mix-blend-mode: var(--tweak-text-block-b
 lend )\; } @media screen and (max-width: 767px) { #block-b8b758de027f728d7
 d53 { } } @media screen and (max-width: 767px) { #block-b8b758de027f728d7d
 53 .sqs-html-content { } } @media screen and (max-width: 767px) { }\nURL: 
 https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/events/ride-the-loop
LOCATION:Fix Coffee + Bikes\, 486 Front Street West\, Toronto\, ON\, M5V 0
 V2\, Canada
URL:https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/events/ride-the-loop
END:VEVENT
