BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cycling Good Cheer Holiday Bicycle Ride
DTSTART:20241208T163000Z
DTEND:20241208T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20241128T181325Z
UID:3cb160e3-9847-5654-ae06-1046ed828600
DESCRIPTION:[ { "shape": "underline"\, "isFront": false\, "isAnimationEnab
 led": false\, "animation": "draw"\, "duration": 0.5\, "direction": "right"
 \, "color": { "type": "THEME_COLOR" }\, "thickness": { "unit": "em"\, "val
 ue": 0.1 }\, "linecap": "square"\, "type": "highlight"\, "id": "955e8ac0-b
 65b-4119-a44c-62c129377b47" } ]\n\nJoin our 5th annual Cycling Good Cheer 
 holiday bicycle ride through Toronto.\n\nBegin with us at one of four loca
 tions:\n\nWEST END with Santa Claus\, elves\, and of course reindeer! Meet
  at Mabelle Park\, 38 Mabelle Ave\, at 11 am for free hot chocolate and co
 okies. Get a photo with Santa and the elves! Please bring a non-perishable
  food or toy donation if possible. Santa will fly (roll) leaving at 11:45 
 am from Mabelle Park\, then ride east along Bloor Street.\n\nEAST END with
  the Grinch beginning at the northwest corner of Victoria Park and Danfort
 h. at Noon. Join us for a decorating party on Saturday\, November 30. Emai
 l (mailto:toeastcyclists@gmail.com) toeastcyclists@gmail.com for details.\
 n\nCENTRAL meetup with the Kidical Mass ride and our Toronto Bicycle Mayor
 . Look for all the kids in Christie Pits Park at 12 noon for a 12:30 depar
 ture as Santa cycles by!\n\nNORTH POLE aka NORTH YORK\, Lawrence Ave at Yo
 nge St\, leaving at 12:15 pm.\n\nThe rides will converge at St George and 
 Bloor Street at 1pm\, then ride to the finale at Toronto Metropolitan Univ
 ersity.\n\n\n\nAll are welcome to join us and encouraged to dress up in ho
 liday costumes!\n\n\n\n#block-6965156ed63bfc8ca755 { --tweak-text-block-ra
 dius: 0px 0px 0px 0px\; --tweak-text-block-radius: unset\; --stroke-style:
  none\;--stroke-thickness: 6px\; --tweak-text-block-background-color: init
 ial\; } #block-6965156ed63bfc8ca755 .sqs-html-content { --tweak-text-block
