BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:E-bikes: Lots to Love. Let's Deal with the Problems.
DTSTART:20260211T000000Z
DTEND:20260211T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260129T222239Z
UID:b2c21422-69bc-5152-a54f-18bb9a1fe753
DESCRIPTION:Overview\n\nJoin us for a lively evening of discussion about e
 -bikes! Why we love them and love to hate them.\n\nWe want to see e-bike p
 otential maximized\, but how do we deal with the problems\, including powe
 rful\, heavy\, speeding e-bikes in bike lanes that intimidate other riders
 ?\n\nHow should regulation distinguish between pedal-assist e-bikes and mo
 ped- and motorcycle-like e-bikes? Speed? Weight? Power? Acceleration? Or s
 omething else?\n\nOur panel of experts will focus on e-bike technologies\,
  existing regulation and regulation from other jurisdictions\, batteries\,
  the food courier business\, and children on e-bikes.\n\nThe panel will be
  the following:\n\nMC: Dani\, Retailer Perspective: Aaron Enchin (Curbside
  Cycle)\, E-bike batteries: Lance Le Roux (Community Bikeways) E-bike regu
 latory regime: Albert Koehl (lawyer).\n\n#block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 { --t
 weak-text-block-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px\; --tweak-text-block-radius: unset
 \; --stroke-style: none\;--stroke-thickness: 6px\; --tweak-text-block-back
 ground-color: initial\; } #block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 .sqs-html-content { 
 --tweak-text-block-padding: 6% 6% 6% 6%\; --tweak-text-block-padding: init
 ial\; } #block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 { mix-blend-mode: var(--tweak-text-blo
 ck-blend )\; } #block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 { } @media screen and (max-widt
 h: 767px) { #block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 { } } @media screen and (max-width
 : 767px) { #block-eb7887e03a393b03e565 .sqs-html-content { } } @media scre
 en and (max-width: 767px) { }\nURL: https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/eve
 nts/e-bikes-an-evening-discussion-with-curbside-cycle-community-bikeways
LOCATION:Curbside Cycle\, 412 Bloor Street West\, Toronto\, ON\, M5S 1X5\,
  Canada
URL:https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/events/e-bikes-an-evening-discussio
 n-with-curbside-cycle-community-bikeways
END:VEVENT
