BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Future of E-bikes: Community Bikeways + Fix
DTSTART:20260324T223000Z
DTEND:20260325T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T060256Z
UID:d843b8df-9272-510a-9f7a-87c88ef23f54
DESCRIPTION:E-Bikes: Why we love them. Why we hate them (sometimes). And w
 hy we need updated laws about them.\n\nE-bikes are transforming urban tran
 sportation. They offer clean\, affordable and efficient travel\, allowing 
 people of all ages and abilities to go further and faster\, while helping 
 to fight climate change.\n\nBut they are also controversial. Some people s
 ee them as obtrusive and dangerous to pedestrians and other road users.\n\
 nJoin Community Bikeway and Fix Coffee + Bikes for a discussion about the 
 future of e-bikes.\n\nSpeakers: Albert Koehl (Environmental lawyer and aut
 hor of Wheeling through Toronto\, a History of the Bicycle and Its Riders)
 \, Fred Sztabinski/Haydn Wiles (Fix Coffee + Bikes)\, and Lance Le Roux (E
 ngineer\, advocate for e-bikes in condominiums\, and Board member\, Commun
 ity Bikeways).\n\nWhen: Tuesday\, March 24 at 6:30 p.m. (https://www.event
 brite.ca/e/the-future-of-e-bikes-community-bikeways-fix-tickets-1985008763
 647) REGISTER on eventbrite.\n\nWhere: Fix Coffee + Bikes\, 80 Gladstone A
 venue\, Toronto\n\n#block-89ad3a27837ee73183dc { } #block-89ad3a27837ee731
 83dc .sqs-html-content { } #block-89ad3a27837ee73183dc { mix-blend-mode: v
 ar(--tweak-text-block-blend )\; } @media screen and (max-width: 767px) { #
 block-89ad3a27837ee73183dc { } } @media screen and (max-width: 767px) { #b
 lock-89ad3a27837ee73183dc .sqs-html-content { } } @media screen and (max-w
 idth: 767px) { }\nURL: https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/events/the-futur
 e-of-e-bikes-community-bikeways-fix
LOCATION:Fix Coffee + Bikes\, 80 Gladstone Avenue\, Toronto\, ON\, M6J 3K9
 \, Canada
URL:https://www.communitybikewaysto.ca/events/the-future-of-e-bikes-commun
 ity-bikeways-fix
END:VEVENT
